<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.6112/18.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 159.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your
                            Legation’s despatches No. 434 of the 20th ultimo, No. 450 of the 1st,
                            and No. 462 of the 8th<note n="2" xml:id="d451fn2">Not printed; it
                                merely transmitted a pamphlet defending the reclamation project,
                                distributed by the concessionnaire.</note> instant, concerning the
                            Zapata Swamp concession.</p>
                        <p>After receiving letters from Mr. Isaac K. Champion, claiming to represent
                            the concessionary company, and holding a conference with him, the
                            Department has instructed the American Consul General at Habana to make
                            a further investigation of the matter and to <pb facs="0436" n="320" xml:id="pg_320"/> report the result thereof to the Department. He
                            has been directed to confer with you on the subject. You will afford him
                            all necessary assistance and cooperation.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>